From 300945802736006c51c72137d7a04177ef3e3a6b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tushar Darote <tdarote@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Apr 2026 16:45:24 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] tflite/c: Force delegate symbols into tensorflowlite_c library

Adds a dummy source file that references delegate APIs to prevent
link-time symbol stripping from tensorflowlite_c.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [downstream linkage workaround]

This patch is specific to older architectures and build behavior.
Upstream TensorFlow has since changed relevant architecture handling,
and a different fix is implemented upstream:
https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/109379

Signed-off-by: Tushar Darote <tdarote@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 tensorflow/lite/c/CMakeLists.txt            |  1 +
 tensorflow/lite/c/force_delegate_symbols.cc | 56 +++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 57 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 tensorflow/lite/c/force_delegate_symbols.cc

diff --git a/tensorflow/lite/c/CMakeLists.txt b/tensorflow/lite/c/CMakeLists.txt
index c60694931ea..47671fc2eb4 100644
--- a/tensorflow/lite/c/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/tensorflow/lite/c/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -88,6 +88,7 @@ add_library(tensorflowlite_c ${TFLITE_C_LIBTYPE}
   c_api_internal.h
   c_api_types.h
   common.h
+  force_delegate_symbols.cc
 )
 
 if (TFLITE_C_BUILD_SHARED_LIBS)
diff --git a/tensorflow/lite/c/force_delegate_symbols.cc b/tensorflow/lite/c/force_delegate_symbols.cc
new file mode 100644
index 00000000000..56ae5716ee9
--- /dev/null
+++ b/tensorflow/lite/c/force_delegate_symbols.cc
@@ -0,0 +1,56 @@
